title: Be a good friend
author: else
text: i love my friends so clear,  they are to me most dear,  then why do i want it to end? am i being a good friend? i try to figure it out,  but all i can think of is doubt.  my friends are always nice,  so sweet and so precise,  then why do i want it to end? am i being a good friend? they're always there when you're in trouble,  and even when you're not,  they stick with you through freezing weather,  and even really hot.  then why do i want it to end? am i being a good friend? my friends are always loyal,  they're never bratty or spoiled.  they are like sisters and brothers,  but they're not like all the others.  then why do i want it to end? am i being a good friend? it's nice to have an extra shoulder to lean on when you're sad and gloomy,  then why am i suddenly feeling a mix of glum and moody? i want to be the new person that i see,  it is definitely in my grasp,  i am like a time machine,  but one that's stuck in the past.  i see them in my head every single day,  every time i try to get rid of it,  it doesn't go away.  why am i feeling this feeling of regret and even pain,  am i just bound to be who i am right now and never ever change? i am like a bird in a cage with all the other birds,  i want to fly free with the other birds,  but i cannot find the key.  i do really want to change,  but half of me wants to stay the same,  and if i do decide to change,  i'll be whom to blame,  with the feeling of hurt and shame.  then why do i want it to end? am i being a good friend?

title: Water Blossom
author: emma
text: a little cat,  sitting tight.  not letting the cherry blossom out of sight.  drifting down a stream of clear water,  touching a stone,  sticking like sauter.  her blue eyes keen,  her path seen,  to get that cherry blossom.  hopping on stones along,  her pattering paws a rythm to a song.  the pink cherry blossom in the stream,  catching it was like a dream.  i sat blankly and stared as the little cat haired,  straight for the cherry blossom.  her paw in the stream,  though she flicked it back like a silent scream.  her goal so close,  her acheivement the most.  so close,  yet so far away.  her paw back in,  incasing the flower in a furry bin.  she hissed at the water,  determination getting hotter,  her claws spread out full span.  just as she looked,  her littlest claw hooked,  a single petal of that cherry blossom.  her eyes stretched wide,  swelling with pride,  for reaching that cherry blossom.  i looked to see,  i laughed with glee,  the cat had reached the cherry blossom!
